1 AND CASUALTY LOSS RATIO ESTABLISHED UNDER SUBSECTION (B) OF THIS
2 SECTION, THE INSURER SHALL PROVIDE A REBATE TO EACH INSURED IN AN AMOUNT
3 EQUAL TO THE PRODUCT OF:
4 (1) THE TOTAL AMOUNT OF PREMIUM REVENUE RECEIVED BY THE
5 INSURER FROM THE INSURED, AFTER:
6 (I) SUBTRACTING FEDERAL AND STATE TAXES AND LICENSING
7 AND REGULATORY FEES; AND
8 (II) ACCOUNTING FOR PAYMENTS OR RECEIPTS FOR RISK
9 ADJUSTMENT AND REINSURANCE; AND
10 (2) THE DIFFERENCE BETWEEN THE MINIMUM ACCEPTABLE
11 PROPERTY AND CASUALTY LOSS RATIO ESTABLISHED UNDER SUBSECTION (B) OF
12 THIS SECTION AND THE INSURER’S ACTUAL PROPERTY AND CASUALTY LOSS RATIO.
13 (D) THE COMMISSIONER MAY ADOPT REGULATIONS TO CARRY OUT THIS
14 SECTION.
15 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
16 October 1, 2025.

